{{distinguish|Matt Lawton}} {{Use British English|date=January 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Matthew Lowton | image = Matt Lowton.jpg | image_size =200 | caption = Lowton playing for [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] in 2013 | fullname = Matthew John Lowton<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/612828 |title=Updated squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=2 February 2018 |accessdate=10 February 2018}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|6|9|df=y}}<ref name="Hugman2010-11">{{cite book | editor-first = Barry J. | editor-last = Hugman | title = The PFA Footballers' Who's Who 2010–11 | year = 2010 | publisher = Mainstream Publishing | location = Edinburgh | isbn = 978-1-84596-601-0 | page = 259}}</ref> | birth_place = [[Chesterfield]], England | height = {{height|ft=5|in=11}}<ref name="Hugman2010-11"/> | position = [[Defender (association football)#Fullback|Right back]] | currentclub = [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] | clubnumber = 2 | youthyears1 = 1999–2004| youthclubs1 = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]| youthyears2 = 2004–2007| youthclubs2 = [[Sheffield United F.C. Academy|Sheffield United]] | years1 = 2007–2012 | clubs1 = [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] | caps1 = 78 | goals1 = 10 | years2 = 2008 | clubs2 = → [[Sheffield F.C.|Sheffield]] (loan) | caps2 = | goals2 = | years3 = 2009 | clubs3 = → [[Ferencvárosi TC|Ferencváros]] (loan) | caps3 = 5 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2012–2015 | clubs4 = [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] | caps4 = 72 | goals4 = 2 | years5 = 2015– | clubs5 = [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] | caps5 = 104 | goals5 = 1 | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = | club-update = 22:24, 3 January 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = }} '''Matthew John Lowton''' (born 9 June 1989) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] in the [[Premier League]]. He can play in a number of defensive positions but is a natural right-back.{{citation needed|date=August 2018}}
Born in [[Chesterfield]], [[Derbyshire]], Lowton joined [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]]'s [[Sheffield United F.C. Academy|academy]] in 2004. He spent time on [[loan (sports)|loan]] with both non-league [[Sheffield F.C.|Sheffield]] and Hungarian side [[Ferencvárosi TC|Ferencváros]] before making the break into United's first team in 2010. He played regularly for two seasons before being sold to [[Aston Villa]] in 2012. After three seasons and 72 Premier League appearances, he joined Burnley in 2015.
==Playing career==
===Sheffield United=== [[File:Matt Lowton SUFC jrs1967 Owned Image.png|thumb|left|Lowton playing for [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] in 2011]]
Lowton was born in [[Chesterfield]], [[Derbyshire]].<ref name="Hugman2010-11"/> He joined [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] aged fifteen after a spell with [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] and progressed through [[Sheffield United F.C. Academy|Sheffield United's youth set up]] to reserve level, converting from a full-back to a central defensive role in the process.<ref name="blades profile">{{cite web|title=Matthew Lowton&nbsp;– Sheffield United Profile|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=2 January 2008|url=http://origin-www.sufc.premiumtv.co.uk/page/AcademyProfiles/0,,10418~1080223,00.html|accessdate=14 February 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141228194146/http://origin-www.sufc.co.uk/page/AcademyProfiles/0,,10418~1080223,00.html|archivedate=28 December 2014}}</ref> After spending a spell on [[loan (sports)|loan]] at [[Sheffield F.C.|Sheffield FC]] in 2008,<ref name="blades debut"/> in January 2009, Lowton went out on loan to Sheffield United's Hungarian sister club [[Ferencvárosi TC|Ferencváros]], along with fellow reserve player [[Sam Wedgbury]], to get first-team experience. He made his debut in the [[Hungarian Cup|Hungarian League Cup]] the next month,<ref name="fradi debut">{{cite news|title=Kecskemet 0–0 Ferencvaros&nbsp;– match report|url= http://origin-www.sufc.premiumtv.co.uk/page/FerencvarosDetail/0,,10418~1551671,00.html|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date= 10 February 2009|accessdate=10 February 2009}}</ref> making eighteen appearances before returning to United towards the end of the season.
Back in the Championship, Lowton found himself on the fringes of the first team and duly made his Blades debut in a 1–1 draw with [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] at the end of March 2010,<ref name="blades debut">{{cite web|title=Lowton Makes Debut|publisher=Sheffield F.C.|date=25 March 2010|url=http://www.sheffieldfc.com/index.php?view=article&id=1383%3Alowton-makes-debut&option=com_content&Itemid=60|accessdate= 25 April 2011}}</ref> coming on as a late substitute, before making his full debut for the club in the final match of the season.
The following season, Lowton started Sheffield United's opening day fixture, away to [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]], but was issued with a straight red card. Despite this setback, he returned to the first-team picture and was rewarded with a new contract at the end of September.<ref name="new contract">{{cite news|title=Lowton re-signs|url=http://origin-www.sufc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10418~2169121,00.html|publisher=Sheffield United F.C.|date=29 September 2010|accessdate=30 September 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304001900/http://origin-www.sufc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10418~2169121,00.html|archivedate=4 March 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Lowton continued a run of substitute appearances and rewarded United's faith by scoring his first senior goal in mid-October, netting in a 3–3 home draw with [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].<ref name="debut goal">{{cite news|title=Sheer elation for Matt|url=http://www.sheffieldunited-mad.co.uk/news/tmnw/sheer_elation_for_matt_570468/index.shtml|publisher=Sheffield United Mad|date=17 October 2010|accessdate=7 November 2010}}</ref> Lowton played regularly for the remainder of the season, scoring four goals in all, but couldn't prevent the club from slipping to relegation.
With the Blades in [[Football League One|League One]] at the time, Lowton remained a key player and was rewarded with an extended contract in August 2011,<ref name="new deal">{{cite news|title=Lowton sets his sights on top-flight after signing deal|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/sheffield-united/lowton_sets_his_sights_on_top_flight_after_signing_deal_1_3672601|publisher=The Sheffield Star|date=12 August 2011|accessdate=12 August 2010}}</ref> making 55 appearances in total for the Blades during the following season and scoring six goals.<ref name="last blades stats">{{Soccerbase season|53439|2011|name=Matthew Lowton|accessdate=29 December 2013}}</ref>
===Aston Villa=== Lowton completed a move to [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] in July 2012 for an undisclosed fee, believed to be £3&nbsp;million, becoming [[Paul Lambert]]'s second signing as Villa manager,<ref name="villa">{{cite news|title=Lowton Signs for Aston Villa|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2169653/Matthew-Lowton-signs-Aston-Villa.html|work=Daily Mail|date=6 July 2012|accessdate=6 July 2012}}</ref> and made his debut on 18 August 2012, in the [[Premier League]] against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].<ref name="villa debut">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19221467|title=West Ham 1–0 Aston Villa|publisher=BBC Sport|date=18 August 2012|accessdate=15 September 2012}}</ref> On 15 September, Lowton scored his first league goal for Villa in a 2–0 home win against [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]].<ref name="villa goal">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19528067|title=Aston Villa 2–0 Swansea|publisher=BBC Sport|date=15 September 2012|accessdate=15 September 2012}}</ref> On 19 July 2013, Lowton signed a new four-year deal to keep him at Aston Villa until the summer of 2017.{{citation needed|date=December 2018}}
===Burnley=== On 22 June 2015, [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] secured the signing of Lowton on a three-year deal for an undisclosed fee believed to be around £1&nbsp;million plus add-ons.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Clarets Complete Lowton Swoop |url=http://www.burnleyfootballclub.com/news/article/clarets-complete-lowton-swoop-2502763.aspx |publisher=Burnley F.C. |date=22 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11708/9892396/sky-sources-villas-lowton-close-to-burnley-move|title=Aston Villa defender Matt Lowton set to join Burnley}}</ref> Lowton made his debut for Burnley on 20 October, as an 84th-minute substitute against [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]]; his first start came against [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]] on 19 December.<ref name=sb1516>{{Soccerbase season|53439|2015|name=Matthew Lowton|accessdate=23 June 2015}}</ref> His first and only goal of the season was Burnley's fourth in a 5–0 rout of [[Milton Keynes Dons F.C.|Milton Keynes Dons]] on 12 January 2016.<ref name=sb1516 /> Lowton would make 27 appearances in his maiden season at Burnley, all in the League,<ref name=sb1516 /> as Burnley won the Football League Championship title and earned promotion to the Premier League.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36176219|title=Charlton 0–3 Burnley|publisher=BBC Sport|date=7 May 2016|accessdate=13 May 2018}}</ref>
